vars:pre-request {
  masterDataId: "b8820bc4-718a-4324-9c94-d610d5bdf2f2
}

script:post-response {
  const data = res.getBody() && res.getBody().data;
  if (data && data.id) bru.setEnvVar("labTestId", data.id);
}

tests {
  test("201 Created", function () {
    expect(res.getStatus()).to.equal(201);
  });
}

docs {
  Create a lab test inside a master data (tenant/branch from the JWT + the path's
  master data). Captures `labTestId`. Children (`samples`, `resultParams`, each
  param's `referenceRanges`/`referenceValues`) are created in the same
  transaction; the response includes them all, plus a seeded `versionHistory` v1.
  
  This body is the **full field set the Add Test form (kaltros-fe) can send**, so
  it doubles as the FE↔BE contract reference. `isMandatoryTest` is `true` here so
  the three mandatory-scope ids (`mandatoryDeptId`/`mandatoryCatId`/
  `mandatorySubcatId`) are shown; set it `false` and drop them when not needed.
  
  ## Field groups (form section → payload)
  
  - **Basic Details:** `testName`, `testDisplayName`, `testCode`, `aka`,
    `departmentId`/`categoryId`/`subCategoryId`, `processMethod`, `icdCode`,
    `loincCode`, `clinicalTags[]`, `samplePriorityType`, `isEnableCms`,
    `isMandatoryTest` (+ `mandatoryDeptId`/`mandatoryCatId`/`mandatorySubcatId`),
    `isHideInOrderScreen`, `isRepeatIntervalRestriction` (+ `repeatIntervalValue`
    + `repeatIntervalUnit`).
  - **Pricing:** `priceMsrp`, `priceMaximum`, `priceMinimum`, `priceOriginal`,
    `franchisePrice`, `emergencyPrice`, `commissionPrice`, `discountCapPct`,
    `isAllowPriceOverride`.
  - **TAT:** `tatMinValue`/`tatMinUnit`, `tatMaxValue`/`tatMaxUnit`,
    `scheduleDays[]`, `scheduleFrom`/`scheduleTo`, `procTimeMinValue`/
    `procTimeMinUnit`, `procTimeMaxValue`/`procTimeMaxUnit`,
    `approvalTimeFrom`/`approvalTimeTo`.
  - **Flags:** `isAllowDiscounts`, `isPreferenceTest`, `isActive` (Active/Inactive).
  - **Notes:** `usefulFor`, `interpretationOfResults`, `limitations`, `remarks`,
    `references`.
  - **Samples[]:** `sampleType`, `containerType`, `sampleSize`,
    `collectionMethod`, `numberOfSamples`, `stability`, `transportTemperature`,
    `preservative`, `sampleHandlingInstructions`, `isFastingRequired`,
    `isLightProtection`, `isDefault`.
  - **Result params[]:** `groupName`, `parameterName`, `parameterCode`, `method`,
    `reportingUnit`, `resultType`, `parameterType`, `resultEntryMode`,
    `calculationFormula` (required when `parameterType=CALCULATED`),
    `resultRoundingType`, `allowableUnits`, `decimalPlaces`, `criticalMin`,
    `criticalMax`, `reflexTests[]`, `notes`, `isNabl`, `isCap`, `sortOrder`,
    `referenceRanges[]`, `referenceValues[]`.
  
  ## Logical-reference ids (no existence check on create)
  
  `departmentId`/`categoryId`/`subCategoryId` and the `mandatory*Id` trio are
  optional UUID **logical refs** — validated as UUIDs but not FK-checked here.
  Replace the placeholder ids above with real ones from
  `GET /departments` · `/categories` · `/sub-categories`. The 8 settings/template
  ids (reportTemplateId, pdfSettingsId, imageSettingsId, approvalWorkflowId,
  groupLayoutId, groupSettingsId, iconSettingsId, sampleNameId) are likewise
  optional logical refs — omit until those modules exist.
  
  ## Reflex tests
  
  Each result param may carry `reflexTests: [{ id, name }]`. The whole array is
  stored verbatim as a **JSON snapshot** (the `reflex_tests` column) and returned
  as-is on read — the backend does not extract ids into a relational column or
  resolve names. `id` must be a valid UUID and `name` a non-empty string, but the
  id is **not existence-checked** against lab tests. (The old bare
  `reflexTestIds: string[]` array input is no longer accepted.)
  
  ## Enums (UPPERCASE)
  
  `processMethod` (SINGLE_STEP|MULTI_STEP), `samplePriorityType`
  (ROUTINE|URGENT|STAT), `tat*Unit`/`procTime*Unit` (MINUTES|HOURS|DAYS),
  `repeatIntervalUnit` (HOURS|DAYS|MONTHS|YEARS), `scheduleDays` (MONDAY…SUNDAY),
  `containerType`, `resultType` (QUANTITATIVE|QUALITATIVE|CALCULATED),
  `parameterType` (MEASURED|CALCULATED), `resultEntryMode` (MANUAL|AUTO),
  `resultRoundingType` (NO_ROUNDING|ONE_DECIMAL|TWO_DECIMAL|THREE_DECIMAL|WHOLE_NUMBER),
  `gender` (ALL|MALE|FEMALE), `age*Unit` (DAYS|MONTHS|YEARS), `abnormalFlagLogic`
  (BOLD_AND_RED|BOLD_ONLY|ITALIC|UNDERLINE|COLOUR_HIGHLIGHT).
  
  ## Conflicts & cross-field rules
  
  - `testName` (2-255) / `testCode` (1-50) unique **per master data** among active
    rows → 409 `LAB_TEST_NAME_CONFLICT` / `LAB_TEST_CODE_CONFLICT`;
    `parameterCode` unique per test → 409 `LAB_TEST_PARAM_CODE_CONFLICT`.
  - `priceMaximum ≤ priceMsrp`, `priceMinimum ≤ priceMaximum` (422).
  - `isMandatoryTest: true` requires `mandatoryDeptId` (422).
  - `isRepeatIntervalRestriction: true` requires `repeatIntervalValue` +
    `repeatIntervalUnit` (422).
  - A `CALCULATED` parameter requires `calculationFormula` (422).
  - Per result param: `criticalMin ≤ criticalMax` (422).
  - Per range: `lowerLimit ≤ upperLimit`, `criticalMin ≤ lowerLimit`,
    `criticalMax ≥ upperLimit`, `ageFrom ≤ ageTo` (422).
}
